getLength().Description: The number of DOMImplementations in the list. The range of valid child node indices is 0 to length-1 inclusive.

Returns: The DOMImplementation at the index th position in the DOMImplementationList, or null if that is not a valid index.
item(int).Description: Returns the indexth item in the collection. If index is greater than or equal to the number of DOMImplementations in the list, this returns null.
